title: Hancock Collects 2nd #ASunMGolf Weekly Honor of Season
text: Hancock Collects 2nd #ASunMGolf Weekly Honor of Season Story Links Taylor Hancock picked up his second career Atlantic Sun Men's Golfer of the Week award following his outstanding play at the Shoal Creek Invitational this past week, the league office announced on Thursday.Hancock led North Florida with a three-under par 213 total which was good enough to finish in a tie for third place. He was the highest UNF finisher as the Ospreys closed strong to finish in second in the 12-team field. After shooting a 76 in the opening round, Hancock fired back-to-back rounds in the 60's to move up the leaderboard."Taylor had another great week," said Osprey head coach Scott Schroeder . "He got off a slow start but bounced back nicely to almost win the event. Taylor has shown signs of great growth as a player this season."Hancock finished with 13 birdies combined in his three rounds, which ranked him second among all golfers in the tournament. He played the par 5 holes at five-under par for the tournament, also second best in the field. His third place finish marked his sixth career top-10 showing. He lowered his season stroke average to 72.33 and his back-to-back rounds of 68 and 69 were the 11th and 12th time he recorded a round under 70. The Ospreys will take a couple weeks off before returning to action at the Tavistock Collegiate Invitational at Isleworth Country Club on Oct. 18-20. Atlantic Sun Men's Golfer of the Week - Oct. 1st
